{"article_id":"pCTGLQ0e4EaYitpp","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"With a Russian plan","depth":8},{"id":1,"text":"to peacefully address Syria ' s chemical weapons suddenly grabbing the global stage ,","depth":8},{"id":2,"text":"President Obama modified an address to the American people Tuesday evening from what was to have been a laser-like focus on military intervention","depth":7},{"id":3,"text":"to include a vision","depth":7},{"id":4,"text":"of how diplomacy might yet work .","depth":7},{"id":5,"text":"But in a crisp 15-minute East Room speech , Mr. Obama still pressed to make the case to a war-weary public","depth":6},{"id":6,"text":"that stopping the use and spread of Syria ' s chemical weapons is of such vital national interest","depth":7},{"id":7,"text":"that military action may yet be necessary .","depth":7},{"id":8,"text":"\" Our ideals and principles , as well as our national security , are at stake in Syria , \"","depth":7},{"id":9,"text":"Obama said ,","depth":7},{"id":10,"text":"adding","depth":9},{"id":11,"text":"that not addressing what he said","depth":10},{"id":12,"text":"was Syrian leader Bashar al-Assad ' s proven use of chemical weapons last month would loosen the decades-old global ban on such use .","depth":10},{"id":13,"text":"It could eventually leave US troops vulnerable to attacks by such weapons ,","depth":10},{"id":14,"text":"he added ,","depth":10},{"id":15,"text":"and lead other countries , such as Iran , to believe","depth":10},{"id":16,"text":"they can pursue weapons of mass destruction ,","depth":12},{"id":17,"text":"including nuclear weapons ,","depth":12},{"id":18,"text":"with impunity .","depth":11},{"id":19,"text":"\" A failure","depth":11},{"id":20,"text":"to stand against the use of chemical weapons","depth":11},{"id":21,"text":"would weaken the prohibitions on other weapons of mass destruction , \"","depth":10},{"id":22,"text":"he said ,","depth":9},{"id":23,"text":"citing Iran and its nuclear program ,","depth":9},{"id":24,"text":"which the US and other Western powers suspect","depth":10},{"id":25,"text":"is aimed at developing a nuclear bomb .","depth":10},{"id":26,"text":"Obama cited some of what he said","depth":7},{"id":27,"text":"were the many expressions of opposition to military action","depth":8},{"id":28,"text":"he has received ,","depth":9},{"id":29,"text":"including from veterans ,","depth":9},{"id":30,"text":"making clear","depth":7},{"id":31,"text":"that he understands the uphill battle","depth":9},{"id":32,"text":"he faces","depth":9},{"id":33,"text":"to convince a skeptical public .","depth":8},{"id":34,"text":"Just hours before he addressed the nation ,","depth":7},{"id":35,"text":"he appeared to be on the verge of losing a vote in Congress","depth":8},{"id":36,"text":"authorizing the use of force in Syria ,","depth":8},{"id":37,"text":"and the sudden diplomatic gambit , in the form of a Russian proposal for international control and eventual destruction of Syria ' s substantial chemical weapons stockpiles , clearly made the case for the use of force that much more difficult .","depth":6},{"id":38,"text":"But the president said","depth":6},{"id":39,"text":"now is no time","depth":7},{"id":40,"text":"to take military action off the table .","depth":7},{"id":41,"text":"If 11th -hour diplomatic efforts on Syria are fruitful ,","depth":6},{"id":42,"text":"it will be because the US prodded key players in the crisis","depth":8},{"id":43,"text":"- notably Russia and Mr. Assad -","depth":8},{"id":44,"text":"into action","depth":8},{"id":45,"text":"by threatening an imminent use of force ,","depth":8},{"id":46,"text":"he said .","depth":5},{"id":47,"text":"Obama said","depth":5},{"id":48,"text":"his administration will be at the forefront of diplomatic efforts over the coming days :","depth":5},{"id":49,"text":"Secretary of State John Kerry will travel to Geneva Thursday","depth":6},{"id":50,"text":"to meet with Russian Foreign Minister Sergei Lavrov ,","depth":6},{"id":51,"text":"the US will work at the United Nations","depth":7},{"id":52,"text":"to forge a Security Council resolution","depth":8},{"id":53,"text":"to compel Syria to give up its chemical weapons ,","depth":8},{"id":54,"text":"and Obama will pursue discussions with Russian President Vladimir Putin about the diplomatic path forward .","depth":6},{"id":55,"text":"Mr. Putin said earlier Tuesday","depth":5},{"id":56,"text":"that a plan","depth":8},{"id":57,"text":"to take control of and destroy Syria ' s chemical weapons","depth":8},{"id":58,"text":"could only work","depth":7},{"id":59,"text":"if the US committed to taking no military action against Syria .","depth":6},{"id":60,"text":"\" Undoubtedly , all of this","depth":11},{"id":61,"text":"[ proposal ]","depth":12},{"id":62,"text":"makes sense","depth":12},{"id":63,"text":"and can function ,","depth":11},{"id":64,"text":"can work ,","depth":11},{"id":65,"text":"only if we hear","depth":9},{"id":66,"text":"that the American side","depth":10},{"id":67,"text":"and those","depth":11},{"id":68,"text":"who support the United States in this sense","depth":11},{"id":69,"text":"rule out the use of force , \"","depth":9},{"id":70,"text":"Putin said in televised remarks .","depth":7},{"id":71,"text":"That would be true ,","depth":8},{"id":72,"text":"he added ,","depth":8},{"id":73,"text":"\" because it is difficult to make any country","depth":10},{"id":74,"text":"- Syria or any other country , any other government in the world -","depth":10},{"id":75,"text":"unilaterally disarm","depth":9},{"id":76,"text":"if the use of force is being prepared against it . \"","depth":8},{"id":77,"text":"But Obama made clear in his televised speech","depth":6},{"id":78,"text":"that the US must remain ready to take military steps","depth":8},{"id":79,"text":"to deter any future use of chemical weapons in Syria ,","depth":8},{"id":80,"text":"if diplomacy fails .","depth":7},{"id":81,"text":"In the hours","depth":7},{"id":82,"text":"leading up to Obama ' s speech ,","depth":7},{"id":83,"text":"many congressional leaders and political analysts said","depth":6},{"id":84,"text":"the president would have to answer the public ' s specific doubts about military intervention .","depth":5},{"id":85,"text":"As if on cue , the president listed and responded to what he said","depth":7},{"id":86,"text":"were the main questions","depth":8},{"id":87,"text":"he had heard from Americans in recent days :","depth":8},{"id":88,"text":"To concerns","depth":8},{"id":89,"text":"about America finding itself once again on a \" slippery slope \" to drawn-out war ,","depth":8},{"id":90,"text":"Obama pledged","depth":8},{"id":91,"text":"there would be \" no boots on the ground , \"","depth":9},{"id":92,"text":"not even an extended air campaign as in the cases of Libya or Kosovo .","depth":9},{"id":93,"text":"To those","depth":9},{"id":94,"text":"who worry","depth":10},{"id":95,"text":"that doing too little will do nothing","depth":11},{"id":96,"text":"to alter Assad ' s behavior ,","depth":11},{"id":97,"text":"Obama said ,","depth":9},{"id":98,"text":"\" The US military doesn ' t do pinpricks , \"","depth":9},{"id":99,"text":"and he insisted","depth":8},{"id":100,"text":"that the US is the only country","depth":9},{"id":101,"text":"that can deliver the message","depth":10},{"id":102,"text":"that Assad needs to hear .","depth":10},{"id":103,"text":"As to why the US shouldn ' t leave this crisis to other players ,","depth":8},{"id":104,"text":"Obama said","depth":10},{"id":105,"text":"he agrees","depth":11},{"id":106,"text":"that the US \" should not be the world ' s policeman . \"","depth":11},{"id":107,"text":"\" I have a deeply held preference for peaceful solutions , \"","depth":11},{"id":108,"text":"he said .","depth":11},{"id":109,"text":"But he added","depth":12},{"id":110,"text":"that \" for nearly seven decades the US has been the anchor of international security , \"","depth":12},{"id":111,"text":"and he said","depth":12},{"id":112,"text":"the world is better for the values and principles","depth":13},{"id":113,"text":"the US has used its power","depth":14},{"id":114,"text":"to promote .","depth":14},{"id":115,"text":"Yet","depth":9},{"id":116,"text":"as stirring as such words may be ,","depth":10},{"id":117,"text":"they seemed unlikely to be enough","depth":12},{"id":118,"text":"to sway a deeply dubious public ,","depth":12},{"id":119,"text":"as many analysts were already concluding after the speech .","depth":11},{"id":120,"text":"Moreover , the promise of a diplomatic solution","depth":11},{"id":121,"text":"that upstaged Obama 's own efforts ,","depth":11},{"id":122,"text":"seemed likely to fade","depth":10},{"id":123,"text":"as it faces scrutiny over questions","depth":11},{"id":124,"text":"ranging from how Syria ' s chemical weapons could be verifiably controlled","depth":11},{"id":125,"text":"to how any agreement would seem to legitimize Assad ' s hold on power .","depth":10},{"id":126,"text":"Some analysts quickly criticized the speech","depth":5},{"id":127,"text":"for leaving unanswered critical questions about the prospects for diplomacy .","depth":5},{"id":128,"text":"Obama left out \" two huge pieces \"","depth":6},{"id":129,"text":"by failing to define what criteria he will use","depth":8},{"id":130,"text":"to judge the Russian initiative","depth":8},{"id":131,"text":"and how much time he intends to give diplomacy ,","depth":7},{"id":132,"text":"says Kenneth Pollack of Washington ' s Brookings Institution .","depth":5},{"id":133,"text":"Get the Monitor Stories","depth":6},{"id":134,"text":"you care about","depth":6},{"id":135,"text":"delivered to your inbox .","depth":5},{"id":136,"text":"By signing up ,","depth":5},{"id":137,"text":"you agree to our Privacy Policy","depth":5},{"id":138,"text":"The public , Congress , and the military need to know","depth":7},{"id":139,"text":"\" how long he intends to give [ diplomacy ] to succeed or fail","depth":8},{"id":140,"text":"so that we can know","depth":9},{"id":141,"text":"whether we are going to use force in Syria and when , \"","depth":9},{"id":142,"text":"Mr. Pollack adds .","depth":6},{"id":143,"text":"\" Cliff-hangers might make for great movies ,","depth":7},{"id":144,"text":"but the president owes the country more from a speech on the use of force . \"","depth":7},{"id":145,"text":"Obama said in his speech","depth":7},{"id":146,"text":"that responding to the Assad regime 's use of chemical weapons is an issue of US national security interest .","depth":7},{"id":147,"text":"In any case , it ' s an issue","depth":5},{"id":148,"text":"that promises to be around for some time","depth":6},{"id":149,"text":"to come .","depth":6}],"relations":[{"parent":299,"left":230,"right":298,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":230,"left":196,"right":229,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":196,"left":183,"right":195,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":183,"left":157,"right":182,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":157,"left":154,"right":156,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":154,"left":152,"right":153,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":152,"left":151,"right":2,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":151,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":153,"left":3,"right":4,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":156,"left":5,"right":155,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":155,"left":6,"right":7,"relation":"causal","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":182,"left":174,"right":181,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":174,"left":158,"right":173,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":158,"left":8,"right":9,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":173,"left":166,"right":172,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":166,"left":160,"right":165,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":160,"left":10,"right":159,"relation":